dismissalText.commentary: Andy McBrine lbw b Rashid Khan 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: McBrine looks to get forward and defend the ball, misses it with the bat and is hit on the pad. Everyone of the Afghan players appeal and Umpire Renyolds finger goes up

commentTextItems.html: Murtagh gets a thick edge on the ball, it flies past the slip and it keeps on going. Murtagh comes back for the second and Ireland win!

commentPostTextItems.html: Simi Singh was unbeaten for the first time in an ODI, guided the tail well to help Ireland eek out a nervy three wicket win over Afghanistan.
Andrew Balbirnie was the top batsman on show today and his classy 60 off 93 balls set up the base for Ireland, there was a couple of wobbles with wickets falling in clusters.
Yet the truth is that Afghanistan never really had enough runs to defend, and although Rashid picked up another three wickets, Ireland were always ahead of the run-rate.
It really goes to show that you don't need to be scoring a mountain of runs to have an exciting game. Who doesn't love a low scoring thriller?
Its now one-one in the series, with the final game this Friday. I'll be here and I hope that you will be able to join me too. This is Justin saying goodnight from Stormont.

commentTextItems.html: clips down the legside, Zazai fields
its speared down the legside and Shahzad has no chance to stop that, Zazai can't cut it off either and it runs to the rope
backs away and cuts the ball out to deep point, Naib gets the ball back in. Seven needed now
backs away and plays the ball back to the bowler
back in the crease, hits the ball up to mid-wicket
huge appeal for LBW from Mujeeeb, looks like it might have been doing too much but the Afghan's can't believe its not been given. Think that they all need to calm down out there!

commentPostTextItems.html: More chats between the Umpires and Singh out there. Could be lots for the match referee to do after the game....

commentTextItems.html: Shahzad whips of the bails, looks like he has Murtagh stumped. He is delighted but they go upstairs to check, looks like Murtagh's back foot was just in. On we go...
clips the ball off the pads and through square leg
outside off-stump, pushes out at the ball and it takes the edge, goes past the slips and the target is into single figures now
onto the front foot and defends the ball into the covers
clips the pad and rolls down past the keeper, another run gets chalked off
it yet another short ball, Murtagh seems to take his eye's off the ball, could have hit him on his helmet or shoulder. Hard to tell from here, they run through anyway

commentTextItems.html: stays deep in the crease, Alam is looking to get the ball down at his feet and itd dug out
defends the ball back up the pitch
Alam goes short to Singh, it doesn't bounce much off the pitch and its played out to deep point
Its on legstump and Murtagh calmly clips the ball into the legside, no-one at mid-wicket to stop the single
comes round the wicket and spears the ball wide down the legside, brings the target down by one
full toss, Singh swings the bat at the ball and pulls it down towards long leg, there is a fielder down there and they keep the batsmen to one
it hits Murtagh on the pads and Rashid appeals as he runs down towards Murtagh, Umpire Reynolds just shakes his head and that's Rashid bowled out now.

dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling st †Mohammad Shahzad b Mohammad Nabi 39 (50b 3x4 1x6 58m) SR: 78

dismissalComment.html: and there is the big wicket. Stirling looks to get forward to the ball, the ball spins past the bat and Shahzad whips off the bails. Looks like they are checking to see if Nabi overstepped. It takes ages but the Umpires finally give it.

dismissalText.commentary: Niall O'Brien c sub (Shafiqullah) b Mohammad Nabi 10 (20b 1x4 0x6 24m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: although he isn't going to be needed! Its a bit of a nothing ball from Nabi, O'Brien picks out extra cover perfectly and Ireland lose their third wicket.
